# API Contracts

## Schema-First

`api/openapi.yaml` is the single source of truth (OpenAPI 3.0.1). All API types are generated — never written by hand.

| | Tool | Output | Do not modify |
|---|---|---|---|
| Backend | `oapi-codegen` | `internal/api/server.gen.go` | yes |
| Frontend | `@hey-api/openapi-ts` | `frontend/src/lib/api/` (entire dir) | yes |

Custom wiring (config, error helpers, query keys) lives in `frontend/src/lib/api-client/`.

## Regeneration

Always regenerate after changing `api/openapi.yaml`:
- `make api` — regenerates both backend and frontend types in one step
- Or separately: `go generate ./internal/api` / `cd frontend && npm run generate:api`

Note: `npm run dev` and `npm run build` automatically run `generate:api` via pre-scripts. Backend types are never auto-regenerated — always run `make api` after spec changes.

## Spec Conventions

- Use `operationId` on every endpoint (drives type and function naming in generated code)
- Use `$ref` for reusable schemas in `components/schemas/`
- Include validation in schema (minLength, maxLength, pattern)
- Document all relevant response codes; public endpoints set `security: []`
